SB019990.100 - 1357 - XXXX 4/1/2026 5:03 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 199/VO
1 to the pesticide, if required by regulation under FIFRA;
2 (24) "Nematode" means invertebrate animals of the phylum nemathelminthes and class
3 nematoda, that is, unsegmented round worms with elongated, fusiform, or sac-like
4 bodies covered with cuticle, and inhabiting soil, water, plants, or plant parts; may
5 also be called nemas or eelworms;
6 (25) "Person" means any individual, partnership, association, or any organized group of
7 persons whether incorporated or not;
8 (26) "Pest" means any insect, snail, slug, rodent, nematode, fungus, weed, and any other
9 form of plant or animal life, or virus, bacteria, or other microorganism, except
10 viruses, bacteria, or other microorganisms on or in living man or other living
11 animals, which is normally considered to be a pest, or which the department may
12 declare to be a pest;
13 (27) "Pesticide" means any substance or mixture of substances intended to prevent,
14 destroy, control, repel, attract, or mitigate any pest; any substance or mixture of
15 substances intended to be used as a plant regulator, defoliant, or desiccant; and any
16 substance or mixture of substances intended to be used as a spray adjuvant;
17 (28) "Plant regulator" means any substance or mixture of substances, intended through
18 physiological actions, to accelerate or retard the rate of growth or maturation, or to
19 otherwise alter the behavior of plants, but shall not include substances insofar as
20 they are intended to be used as plant nutrients, trace elements, nutritional chemicals,
21 plant inoculants, or soil amendments;
22 (29) "Protect health and the environment" means protection against any unreasonable
23 adverse effects on the environment;
24 (30) "Registrant" means a person who has registered any pesticide pursuant to the
25 provisions of KRS 217.542 to 217.630;
26 (31) "Restricted-use pesticide" means any pesticide classified for restricted use by the
27 administrator, EPA, or by regulation of the department;
Page 6 of 7
SB019990.100 - 1357 - XXXX 4/1/2026 5:03 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 199/VO
1 (32) "Spray adjuvant" means any wetting agent, spreading agent, sticker, deposit builder,
2 adhesive, emulsifying agent, deflocculating agent, water modifier, or similar agent
3 intended to be used with any other pesticide as an aid to the application or to the
4 effect thereof, and which is in a package or container separate from that of the other
5 pesticide with which it is to be used;
6 (33) "Unreasonable adverse effects on the environment" means any unreasonable risk to
7 man or the environment, taking into account the economic, social, and
8 environmental costs and benefits of the use of any pesticide;
9 (34) "Weed" means any plant which grows where not wanted; and
10 (35) "Wildlife" means all living things that are neither human, domesticated, nor as
11 defined in KRS 217.542 to 217.630, pests, including but not limited to mammals,
12 birds, and aquatic life.
